However, these stresses may make key organisms more vulnerable to chronic (long-term, low-level, and perhaps undetectable52) stresses created by human populations (sedimentation, nutrification, overfishing, etc.).
Moreover, natural and human stresses may interact synergistically, combining substances or factors which separately may be relatively harmless, but when added together can be more potent and magnify impacts in unpredictable ways.
