the shallower reefs are most affected.
Except for shallow reefs off Florida, the CNMI, Palau, and Palmyra, mortality from bleaching episodes has generally been low.
On the other hand, current marginal subtropical reefs where coral calcification temperatures are below optimum may not only survive, but benefit from global climate change (J. Maragos and D. Siciliano pers. comm.).
Cooler water reefs off the NWHI and perhaps deeper reefs such as the Flower Garden Banks should be buffered from the effects of coral bleaching when surface waters warm.
