Damage to coral reef ecosystems from tourist activities is inevitable.
Impacts range from coastal development (e.g., hotels, marinas) to boating and other recreational activities.
Rental boats are a problem, as tourists unfamiliar with piloting vessels in and around shallow waters with coral reefs run aground or collide with corals.
SCUBA divers, snorkelers, underwater tours using surface-supplied equipment, and a large number of personal watercraft (i.e., jet skis) have all affected reefs and water quality.
Harmful as they may be, damage from underwater reef-snorkeling tours and anchoring in most areas
